Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.50,0:00:31.05,Default,,0,0,0,,We say Gloria and Excelsius Dio.\NAll praise be to thee, O Lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.14,0:00:34.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Amen.\NI asked the Lord if I should give this lecture today
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.92,0:00:42.54,Default,,0,0,0,,and the arm said yes.\NSo here I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.67,0:00:46.93,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NSo we're going to cover uh basic things
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.93,0:00:53.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and uh we're going to cover them a little differently.\NUh I want things to be uh so familiar
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.46,0:00:58.19,Default,,0,0,0,,that you know it just due to familiarity.\NYou don't have to think.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.23,0:01:03.83,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to memorize anything.\NYou don't have to learn anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.83,0:01:11.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And uh the best teacher is familiarity.\NUh everything just becomes second nature
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.03,0:01:17.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and you don't have to think about it.\NWhere's our slides for today?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.67,0:01:21.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh my god.\NThere we go.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.35,0:01:24.14,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NSo, boy, these are clearer here.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.27,0:01:29.79,Default,,0,0,0,,This is wonderful.\Nuh some places you can't see what the slide is
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.79,0:01:35.18,Default,,0,0,0,,that you're talking about.\NAnyway, we're putting together uh all the slides.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.25,0:01:40.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I think there's 139 of them already.\NAll the lecture slides,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.44,0:01:44.32,Default,,0,0,0,,we're going to put them together\Nand make them available in spiral bound
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.32,0:01:50.63,Default,,0,0,0,,or some kind of printed form because they say\Nthat that when you play the DVD at home,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.63,0:01:55.82,Default,,0,0,0,,you you know it's not clear\Nbecause the camera doesn't pick up sufficient detail.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.89,0:02:01.74,Default,,0,0,0,,So we decided we would make all the uh all of these\Navailable uh to the public.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.84,0:02:05.83,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NSo going back to the basics,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.83,0:02:12.55,Default,,0,0,0,,the basic understanding comes from the nature of\Nconsciousness itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.39,0:02:20.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh so in consciousness then all things are known.\NAll things are knowable.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.55,0:02:26.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Within consciousness all things are are known.\NEverything can be defined.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.40,0:02:36.79,Default,,0,0,0,,The reason this is so is because everything that exists\Nor ever existed gives off an energy field.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.79,0:02:44.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything that ever existed\Nor is now existent gives off a specific energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.55,0:02:52.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Unique, unique, and trackable through all of time.\NAnd this reason for this is has to do with the nature of
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.81,0:03:01.48,Default,,0,0,0,,the infinite field of consciousness itself\Nwhich is poorly un understood even by organizations
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.48,0:03:14.71,Default,,0,0,0,,that devote themselves to the study of consciousness\Nand then never mention mention consciousness again
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.71,0:03:17.61,Default,,0,0,0,,which is just as well bec\Nbecause not one of them address consciousness at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.66,0:03:23.19,Default,,0,0,0,,they all address there's going to be a big conference in\NLondon $40 million or something
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.19,0:03:30.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and uh consciousness will never really be defined\Naccurately uh because what goes on in these conferences
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.22,0:03:33.63,Default,,0,0,0,,has to do with mind.\NSo the failure to differentiate mind
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.63,0:03:40.57,Default,,0,0,0,,which is content from consciousness\Nwhich is context a con for the failure of anything all
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.57,0:03:47.58,Default,,0,0,0,,these attempts at science and consciousness\Nand theology and all don't make progress.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.58,0:03:55.34,Default,,0,0,0,,The infinite field of consciousness then includes all\Nthat has ever been is or could be.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.46,0:04:05.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything leads a trackable track within the infinite\Nfield of consciousness which itself is timeless
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.65,0:04:11.83,Default,,0,0,0,,and non-local.\NWithin the field of consciousness then all time is now
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.83,0:04:21.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and everywhere is here.\NEverywhere is right here into my fingertip.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.27,0:04:25.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Anything anywhere in the universe can be calibrated.\NWhy is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.52,0:04:32.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the tip of my finger is everywhere.\NThere is no beginning, no end.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.38,0:04:40.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And the thing that people have difficulty with is\Nthat consciousness is nonlinear.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.07,0:04:44.66,Default,,0,0,0,,It does not traverse time.\NIt doesn't go from here to there.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.73,0:04:51.43,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't start there or end here.\NIt's everywhere present.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.75,0:05:02.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Now what Cleopatra thought did what she calibrated at is\Nas knowable now as it was at the time of Cleopatra
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.86,0:05:10.76,Default,,0,0,0,,because between then\Nand now there is no time in a nonlinear universe beyond
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.76,0:05:14.11,Default,,0,0,0,,time or dimension.\NAll places are here.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.27,0:05:18.56,Default,,0,0,0,,All time is now.\NIs that simple enough?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.64,0:05:32.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody got that?\NEverywhere is right here and all time is right now
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.87,0:05:38.23,Default,,0,0,0,,because otherwise having distance\Nand time would be linear.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.23,0:05:47.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Linear consciousness is nonlinear.\NSo consciousness is the infinite context.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.74,0:05:53.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that's simple.\NEverybody knows that here.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.43,0:05:55.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody already knows that here.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.74,0:06:03.42,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't have to spend $40 million to find that out.\NThey let me speak today without wearing a red power tie.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.48,0:06:11.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I hope you noticed that.\NI had to pass security clearance.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.97,0:06:19.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Said, "You don't have a red tie.\N" I said, "All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.30,0:06:24.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I forgot my power tie, honey.\NWell, now what am I going to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.62,0:06:27.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Well,\NI will trap the trust in the infinite power of almighty
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.91,0:06:37.51,Default,,0,0,0,,God.\NOh, that'll do.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.30,0:06:53.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything is what it is as a consequence of of\Nthat which it is, not how it's defined or perceived,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.48,0:06:57.89,Default,,0,0,0,,but by virtue of its essence,\Neverything radiates an energy field.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.97,0:07:09.35,Default,,0,0,0,,This energy field radiates itself invisibly.\NIt does not radiate itself across space or time.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.35,0:07:18.41,Default,,0,0,0,,So the things I'm going to ask during the lecture,\Nthe answers already exist prior to my asking the question.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.46,0:07:26.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that simple?\NWith no linear time, there's no before or after,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.28,0:07:28.95,Default,,0,0,0,,no sequence.\NAll of that is a mentalization.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.95,0:07:33.01,Default,,0,0,0,,What is sequent sequential is your mentalization about\Nphenomena.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.07,0:07:38.02,Default,,0,0,0,,The phenomena themselves are not sequential.\NWhat's sequential is your witnessing of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.07,0:07:44.70,Default,,0,0,0,,And because you witness them in a sequential nature,\Nyou think that that's the way the world is sequential.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.80,0:07:48.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NSequential is only how we process it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.62,0:07:54.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything that ever existed exists now\Nand it exists right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.15,0:08:03.87,Default,,0,0,0,,That means then that anything I hold in mind,\Nanything I hold in mind, if it's true, has a match.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.96,0:08:10.39,Default,,0,0,0,,If I hold the statement in mind\Nthat matches what exists in reality,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.39,0:08:17.25,Default,,0,0,0,,then her arm goes strong.\NIf what I'm holding in mind does not match what exists in
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.25,0:08:23.29,Default,,0,0,0,,reality within consciousness itself, her arm goes weak.\NAnd in previous lectures,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.29,0:08:32.33,Default,,0,0,0,,we've tried to outline how this came about uh over the\Nevolution of life on this planet
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.33,0:08:40.38,Default,,0,0,0,,that it was necessary for life to survive to be able to\Ndifferentiate that which is pro-life or true
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.38,0:08:47.74,Default,,0,0,0,,and that which is anti-life or poisonous\Nbecause the little amoeba doesn't know poison from food.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.82,0:08:54.59,Default,,0,0,0,,So he had to learn\Nand so the mind developed uh as a consequence of having
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.59,0:09:00.61,Default,,0,0,0,,to discern that which is pro-life and that\Nwhich is anti-life and the failure to do that means
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.61,0:09:08.12,Default,,0,0,0,,that that life form would expire.\NThat life form would expire and um so we're hoping
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.12,0:09:14.47,Default,,0,0,0,,that mankind will learn the same thing as protozoa\Nand that's why we give these lectures.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.48,0:09:34.86,Default,,0,0,0,," The amiebas made it and bacteria made it.\NTherefore, man can make it, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.98,0:09:38.45,Default,,0,0,0,,So,\Nthey only had to put up with what's negative in nature.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.48,0:09:44.17,Default,,0,0,0,,And we have to put up with what what is negative\Nthat man can create that nature didn't even think of.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.28,0:09:49.10,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what I'm saying?\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.29,0:09:57.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So the uh that we stratified the levels of consciousness\Nas a result of our earliest research back in the 70s
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.42,0:10:02.98,Default,,0,0,0,,when we noticed that some things made people go strong\Nand some people things made people go weak.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.06,0:10:08.99,Default,,0,0,0,,And what what evolved was a stratified uh calibrated\Nlevel of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.99,0:10:14.23,Default,,0,0,0,,that goes from 1 to a thousand\Nwhere where one is merely existence
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.23,0:10:20.87,Default,,0,0,0,,and 1,000 is the highest energy\Nthat exists in this pl in this plane.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.87,0:10:26.75,Default,,0,0,0,,The entities that calibrated a thousand are all the great\Nspiritual teachers of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.84,0:10:33.20,Default,,0,0,0,,the avatars, Jesus Christ, the Buddha,\Nall the great avatars,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.20,0:10:37.17,Default,,0,0,0,,then calibrate at the maximum level possible within the\Nhuman domain.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.24,0:10:42.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Then your energies go beyond that.\NThen you have to go to other dimensions.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.16,0:10:48.76,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't uh this world is not made to handle calibrated\Nenergies over a thousand.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.87,0:10:55.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh then we move move on to the other uh realms move move\Non to the other uh realms which calibrate thou 1,000
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.74,0:11:00.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and even higher uh to the super realms.\NAnyway,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.68,0:11:05.60,Default,,0,0,0,,the map of consciousness allows us then to define\Nanything in a term
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.60,0:11:13.21,Default,,0,0,0,,that we can translate into a calibratable scale\Nwhich is pragmatically useful.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.29,0:11:18.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's one thing to know it and intuitit it\Nand confirm it with the arm
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.76,0:11:23.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and then it's another thing to describe\Nthat fact to somebody else.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.94,0:12:11.30,Default,,0,0,0,," It just glowed with a certain radiance, you know.\NSo, that dog is a 255.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.52,0:12:14.64,Default,,0,0,0,,255.\NSo, we did the arm on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.65,0:12:19.19,Default,,0,0,0,,You can, you know,\Nthe three of us what we'd be like in a dog pound.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.47,0:12:26.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Susan.\NSusan, we should take Kelsey home with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.47,0:12:27.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Resist.\NYep.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.35,0:12:32.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we took Kelsey home with us.\NAnd as usual, the arm was right at 255,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.64,0:12:44.95,Default,,0,0,0,,which exceeds about 3/4 of the human population.\NDoug is friendly, kind response to affection,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.95,0:12:48.55,Default,,0,0,0,,is family oriented,\Nand values love and the good things in life.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.55,0:12:55.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And that sets she's not out to kill anybody\Nor convert anybody.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.99,0:13:03.15,Default,,0,0,0,,She doesn't drive on the highway.\NSo anyway, so what did 255 tell us?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.22,0:13:07.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Well,\Nwe knew that we knew that on our scale of consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.27,0:13:14.62,Default,,0,0,0,,dogs dog was about 250 and a family dog was about 255.\Na family dog, a dog that's been around humans,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.62,0:13:19.70,Default,,0,0,0,,becomes even more conscious,\Nbecomes aware of human uh signals,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.70,0:13:24.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and becomes very smart indeed.\NUh so anyway,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.03,0:13:29.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I just thought I'd tell you\Nthat for what reason I don't remember anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.26,0:13:31.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yes.\NYeah,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.62,0:13:38.94,Default,,0,0,0,,they the family dog calibrates higher than some of the\Npeople who've run for president in past elections.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.94,0:13:46.55,Default,,0,0,0,,They were at 190.\NOur current election, we're pretty pretty lucky.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.59,0:13:50.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody's over everybody's over 200.\NThank God.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.47,0:13:51.15,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NSo,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.15,0:13:56.40,Default,,0,0,0,,we found that the map of consciousness was uh extremely\Nuseful, pragmatically so.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.49,0:14:03.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And uh that anything in the universe\Nthat is ever anything that's ever existed uh
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.28,0:14:09.02,Default,,0,0,0,,or could exist can be calibrated.\NTh this cor corresponded with my training in
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.02,0:14:15.73,Default,,0,0,0,,psychoanalysis and psychiatry\Nbecause Columbia University psychoanalytic clinic called
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.73,0:14:23.72,Default,,0,0,0,,everything below 200 the emergency emotions\Nand everything from 200 and up uh the welfare emotions.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.82,0:14:32.06,Default,,0,0,0,,The welfare emotions produce positive uh responses in the\Nneurologic system
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.06,0:14:36.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and the negative ones bring about bring on pathologic\Nchanges.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.36,0:14:43.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So the view of God\Nwhich you see we put God over here on the left.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.06,0:14:45.57,Default,,0,0,0,,He said he wanted to be on the left.\NI said you want to be on the right left.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.60,0:14:52.29,Default,,0,0,0,,He said put me on the left.\NSo this is people's view of God.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.36,0:14:58.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh and quite a you see how it divides mankind.\NIs God vicious and demands
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.42,0:15:05.46,Default,,0,0,0,,that you rip the beating heart of a virgin uh out of her\Nout and throw her body down the stairs?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.59,0:15:11.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Ancient Mayan Incan religions somehow they always go for\Nyoung virgins.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.88,0:15:17.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Whatever the sacrifice is got to be young virgins.\NYou think some of those religions would run out of young
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.18,0:15:24.23,Default,,0,0,0,,virgins because they tore all their hearts out there.\NWe run out of young virgins here.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.23,0:15:28.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Why does it always have to be a young virgin?\NYou know, not a macho guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.20,0:15:33.59,Default,,0,0,0,,They don't tear out the heart of a macho guy.\NIt's always a harmless little maiden.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.59,0:15:36.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Age 14.\NOh my god.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.94,0:15:45.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh to the view view then of God.\NIs God uh uh vengeful, vindictive, punitive,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.35,0:15:50.04,Default,,0,0,0,,uh uh vengeful, vindictive, punitive, condemning?\NAnd so we run into what are classically the anthrop
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.04,0:15:59.08,Default,,0,0,0,,anthropomorphic depictions of God in which God is blamed.\NWe say how did God get such a negative uh view?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.17,0:16:04.23,Default,,0,0,0,,You know people fear God.\NGod causes catastrophes and disasters and floods
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.23,0:16:10.25,Default,,0,0,0,,and how does uh this all come about?\NIt all came about
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.25,0:16:17.07,Default,,0,0,0,,because primitive man needed an explanation for the\Nphenomena of nature and blamed it on God.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.17,0:16:22.52,Default,,0,0,0,,The gods must be angry.\NThe thunder, the earthquake, the lightning.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.59,0:16:29.03,Default,,0,0,0,,They assumed that it was the angry gods.\NSo the anthropomorphic depictions of divinity
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.03,0:16:33.14,Default,,0,0,0,,which still exist\Nand carry great weight in the minds of many people.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.20,0:16:37.87,Default,,0,0,0,,And they expect in fact\Nthat this god is going to wipe us all out of here in 2012
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.87,0:16:42.08,Default,,0,0,0,,or something.\NWhat do we got to be off this planet?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.35,0:16:47.82,Default,,0,0,0,,2012.\NWe all have to be off this planet by 2012.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.82,0:16:53.06,Default,,0,0,0,,December 21st,\N2012 when the great God of the Incas
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.06,0:17:03.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and you know is going to wipe us all out.\NThe only thing is God might be dead by then
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.78,0:17:09.90,Default,,0,0,0,,and we'll be saved.\NThere's those who believe that God is dead, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.90,0:17:17.87,Default,,0,0,0,,So this the levels of consciousness then explain the\Nmankind's difficulty in understanding the nature of
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.87,0:17:21.70,Default,,0,0,0,,divinity and what man has done primarily is\Nanthropomorphic.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.76,0:17:26.78,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words,\Nhumanlike attributes are then projected onto God.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.78,0:17:34.58,Default,,0,0,0,,God is angry, jealous, fitful, vengeful.\NSo that's the God below calibrated level 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.66,0:17:37.64,Default,,0,0,0,,He's punitive.\NHe gets even with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.69,0:17:39.81,Default,,0,0,0,,He punishes you.\NHe doesn't care about you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.86,0:17:43.27,Default,,0,0,0,,He throws your hell, your soul into hell.\NHe's vindictive.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.34,0:17:46.15,Default,,0,0,0,,He gets even with you.\NHe gets even with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.15,0:17:53.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you imagine a God who gets even with you now?\NYou went and sinned already.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.35,0:17:58.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And you will have to be punished for sinning.\NWhy did man sin?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.73,0:18:08.42,Default,,0,0,0,,because he was created defective.\N" We'd like to know the difference between truth
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.42,0:18:32.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and falsehood.\N" So I said, "Okay, okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.63,0:18:42.33,Default,,0,0,0,,He's going to give you an F in godism.\N" So just in order to curry favor with divinity,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.33,0:18:50.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I put this whole map of consciousness together.\NPlease go God and get off the hook with him, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.60,0:18:55.02,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NSo the view of God then is a reflection of one's
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.02,0:18:59.75,Default,,0,0,0,,understanding which is a reflection of one's evolved\Nlevel of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.75,0:19:06.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Evolved level of consciousness.\NIf mankind is dependent on religious authority to define
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.62,0:19:12.14,Default,,0,0,0,,these attributes of God\Nbecause he did not really understand them himself
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.14,0:19:17.99,Default,,0,0,0,,coherently except for some cultures\Nwhich the world would call primitive who frankly had very
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.99,0:19:21.97,Default,,0,0,0,,evolved understandings of the nature of God.\NThe Native American Indian for one,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.97,0:19:26.38,Default,,0,0,0,,the Native American Indians understanding of God is\Nextremely high.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.45,0:19:31.51,Default,,0,0,0,,God is the allpresent source of life\Nand all is done in the name of God.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.55,0:19:36.70,Default,,0,0,0,,And when you sacrifice an animal,\Nyou do so with reverence to the spirit of the animal
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.70,0:19:41.84,Default,,0,0,0,,and with thanks to God.\NThat's about as evolved a view of God as you can get
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.84,0:19:46.95,Default,,0,0,0,,without a PhD from any theological school.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.95,0:19:58.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh so God is uh loving and wise as infinitely merciful.\NNow what does merciful mean is already in dispute in
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.97,0:20:08.71,Default,,0,0,0,,various cultures uh on the planet right now is it not?\NWhat is the nature of an infinitely merciful God?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.71,0:20:16.08,Default,,0,0,0,,All all merciful God.\NDoes it mean you should behead infidels
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.08,0:20:20.44,Default,,0,0,0,,or merciful means to do them a favor?\NWe'll just behead them.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.49,0:20:34.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, thank you, God, for beheading us all.\NThat was loving and and heartwarming
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.95,0:20:36.08,Default,,0,0,0,,and very very inspiring.\NVery inspiring, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.10,0:20:39.85,Default,,0,0,0,,If you screw up, you'll be beheaded.\NOh, okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.01,0:20:43.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.82,0:20:49.15,Default,,0,0,0,,So,\Ncultural understandings then uh poured down over the
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.15,0:20:58.21,Default,,0,0,0,,centuries whether God is uh anthropomorphic\Nand subject to human anger, resentment and punishment.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.28,0:21:06.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So these are the negative depictions of divinity\Nwhich have great power over large segments of of the
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.07,0:21:12.93,Default,,0,0,0,,world even uh today even today\Nand they predominated in earlier religions
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.93,0:21:21.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and as we said the origin of it was earthquake\Nand flood and catastrophe and primitive man thought
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.46,0:21:28.07,Default,,0,0,0,,that the gods must be angry\Nand therefore they sacrificed more and more virgins
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.07,0:21:34.71,Default,,0,0,0,,and They couldn't keep up with enough virgins to keep God\Nsatisfied.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.51,0:21:42.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Correlated with this view of God is the way you see\Nyourself and the level of consciousness from psychiatry,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.78,0:21:50.16,Default,,0,0,0,,psychoanalysis and other sources.\NThe perennial wisdom calibrates these levels as we always
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.16,0:21:59.11,Default,,0,0,0,,did in psychiatry, psychoanalysis, psychology.\NAt the top is peace and then that is joy and love
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.11,0:22:07.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and reason and acceptance and willingness and above\Nthat and below that neutrality.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.51,0:22:15.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Now the the big uh political thrusts in our society\Ncurrently are in the 300s and they were in the past.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.07,0:22:19.71,Default,,0,0,0,,It's really in the 300s.\NUm who are the 300s?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.80,0:22:23.77,Default,,0,0,0,,The 300s are the volunteer firemen in the city of New\NYork.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.85,0:22:28.33,Default,,0,0,0,,They're the policemen.\NThere's the they're the uh heroic people.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.39,0:22:34.11,Default,,0,0,0,,They're the people who build uh uh big empires.\NThe 300s are very powerful.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.18,0:22:41.51,Default,,0,0,0,,It has to do with doingness and optim optimism.\NIt has to do with uh goodwill.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.62,0:22:46.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Good will, hard work, and service to others.\NSo that's about
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.28,0:22:52.73,Default,,0,0,0,,where both the political parties are right now.\NThey both have an intention uh to serve
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.73,0:23:01.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and to be uh uh a willingness to to be of service\Nand available and both parties I think are in the high
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.16,0:23:08.71,Default,,0,0,0,,300s and I remember the former Clinton administration was\Nalso the ele the elect it's because that's
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.71,0:23:14.86,Default,,0,0,0,,where the electorate is the current American electorate\Nis around seeing as politics is
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.86,0:23:27.19,Default,,0,0,0,,so much uh in the news the current American electorate is\Naround 300 over 370, 375, 374, 373.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.19,0:23:34.53,Default,,0,0,0,,The current American electorate is around 373.\NSo for a political party to win,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.53,0:23:39.38,Default,,0,0,0,,they should aim at that level.\N373 is a very good level.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.43,0:23:47.75,Default,,0,0,0,,And both parties really are pretty much aimed that way.\NSo it's come see kamsa seeing as uh they're both aiming
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.75,0:23:54.87,Default,,0,0,0,,for the same type of uh credible integrous service etc.\NUhhuh.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.15,0:24:05.57,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NSo that level is is harmonious.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.60,0:24:09.59,Default,,0,0,0,,So although things come up sort of negative within\Npolitical campaigns,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.59,0:24:15.93,Default,,0,0,0,,uh it's really uh hopeful\Nand what they're really trying for is harmony
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.93,0:24:21.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and what they're really trying for is optimism.\NOptimism.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.75,0:24:25.35,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NSo that means America's in a good place politically
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.35,0:24:29.39,Default,,0,0,0,,despite what people say about it.\NAnd if you calibrate both parties,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.39,0:24:42.31,Default,,0,0,0,,it won't make much difference who wins.\NIt won't make that much difference.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.35,0:24:43.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?\NBecause America is a great electorate
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.99,0:24:49.85,Default,,0,0,0,,and you can only go so far with the whole public.\NSo you always have the public is a rudder.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.93,0:24:56.47,Default,,0,0,0,,The public is a rudder\Nthat will keep them from from going off on the edge of
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.47,0:24:58.65,Default,,0,0,0,,the cliff.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.74,0:25:06.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So we have the these numbers uh these are mathematical\Nnumbers at the calibrated levels uh
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.28,0:25:11.36,Default,,0,0,0,,which go up to a thousand and go down as far as 20.\NIt even goes below 10.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.41,0:25:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I think Ben Lden is 10.\NYeah, bin Lenon I think is 10.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:16.11,0:25:21.34,Default,,0,0,0,,He he's he's the prize winner in today's he's he's the\Nprize winner in today's negative contest.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.40,0:25:23.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Bin Lden is at 10.\NThere was that mad killer
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.86,0:25:27.83,Default,,0,0,0,,that machine shoot shot everybody.\NHe was about five.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:27.83,0:25:35.19,Default,,0,0,0,,So Ben Len has a has a has a a contestant.\NThat guy that went on video
Dialogue: 0,0:25:35.19,0:25:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and then shot up all his classmates.\NHe calibrated at five.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:38.07,0:25:38.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Cho.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:38.71,0:25:41.45,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Cho.\N>> Cho calibrates at five.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.53,0:25:49.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh Bowen, you just lost the race.\NCho beat boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:50.95,0:25:52.56,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NSo the levels then are very very significant.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.59,0:25:56.35,Default,,0,0,0,,They really tell us a whole uh lot.\NThey're also very reassuring.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:00.55,0:26:04.43,Default,,0,0,0,," And then when you use the arm and you calibrate it,\Nyou see, well, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:04.43,0:26:08.36,Default,,0,0,0,,you can make a lot of different am lot of noise over\Nlittle differences.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:08.42,0:26:14.47,Default,,0,0,0,,But all in all, there's still going to be both around 370.\NWhat did we say the elector was?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:14.55,0:26:15.90,Default,,0,0,0,,373.\N>> 373.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.90,0:26:17.43,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Huh?\N>> 373.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:17.43,0:26:19.75,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Yeah.\NSo, the electorate is at 373.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:19.81,0:26:23.74,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NSo, that's a pretty safe, sensible,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:23.74,0:26:28.54,Default,,0,0,0,,sane uh world to live in.\N373.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:28.54,0:26:36.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh it should bring about peaceful understanding.\NEventually it'll bring about a synthesis of the two
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.32,0:26:39.86,Default,,0,0,0,,parties and you know as far as functioning in the world.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:39.93,0:26:45.35,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's enough of red tie\Nand politics in the world we live in.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:45.35,0:26:50.74,Default,,0,0,0,,How about the next slide?\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.91,0:26:53.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh,\None of the things we did with consciousness calibration,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.69,0:26:59.75,Default,,0,0,0,,one of the first things we did was calibrate the reality\Nof spirit, spiritual realities.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:59.75,0:27:01.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Are there such things as angels?\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:01.75,0:27:04.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Archangels?\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:04.87,0:27:08.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, is there such a thing as heaven?\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:08.62,0:27:14.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Does there more than one heaven?\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:16.63,0:27:19.99,Default,,0,0,0,,So for the first time man could calibrate you know\Ndiscern realities
Dialogue: 0,0:27:19.99,0:27:29.21,Default,,0,0,0,,that are not available to the intellect not available to\Nthe intellect and you solve a lot of uh problems
Dialogue: 0,0:27:29.21,0:27:38.54,Default,,0,0,0,,when you ask certain things like I'll say we have\Npermission to ask there are multiple heavens resist
Dialogue: 0,0:27:38.54,0:27:44.70,Default,,0,0,0,,multiple heavens all right various religious den\Ndenominations have their own neighborhood.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:44.76,0:27:48.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Where's it?\NThey got their own neighborhood.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:48.34,0:28:02.57,Default,,0,0,0,,You know,\Nthe Mormons don't have to mix with the like goes to like.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:02.59,0:28:04.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So those that uh\Nso when the religion tells you you must do a certain
Dialogue: 0,0:28:04.46,0:28:09.66,Default,,0,0,0,,thing in order to get to heaven,\Nwhat they mean is their heaven.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:09.66,0:28:13.20,Default,,0,0,0,,They're talking about their heaven.\NIf you're not a Mormon,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.20,0:28:19.67,Default,,0,0,0,,you're not going to get into Mormon heaven.\NIt doesn't mean you can't get into heaven, period.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:19.72,0:28:22.77,Default,,0,0,0,,It means you can't get into Mormon heaven.\NWell, if you're not a Mormon,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:22.77,0:28:32.47,Default,,0,0,0,,why would you want to go to Mormon heaven anyway?\NSo, there's nothing to feel bad about.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:34.38,0:28:45.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't think there's an atheist heaven, though.\NI suspect there is an agnostic equivalent to heaven.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:45.43,0:28:52.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Those are people who say, "Lord,\NI in and of myself can't make up my mind whether there is
Dialogue: 0,0:28:52.21,0:28:55.46,Default,,0,0,0,,a god or there isn't a god.\N" Well,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:55.46,0:29:01.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I was brought up very religious about as religious as you\Ncan get.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.99,0:29:08.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And then I went through a period of disillusionment\Nand became a dedicated atheist.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.78,0:29:16.54,Default,,0,0,0,,First a dedicated religionist, then a dedicated atheist,\Nthen a dedicated agnostic.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:20.38,0:29:22.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And they say atheism was naive too.\NAgnostic was more sophisticated.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:22.74,0:29:27.68,Default,,0,0,0,,If you can't prove the existence of God one way\Nor the other, you can't say God doesn't exist.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:27.83,0:29:35.55,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not stupid.\NSo you can just say I of myself am unable to know.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:35.62,0:29:41.11,Default,,0,0,0,,So where does agnostic on this thing here?\NWhere is he?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:41.11,0:29:45.54,Default,,0,0,0,,He's not even on there.\NHe's not called an enlightened state.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:45.62,0:29:52.71,Default,,0,0,0,,It's called an intellectually sophisticated state.\NSo the agnostic then represents intellectual
Dialogue: 0,0:29:52.71,0:29:59.41,Default,,0,0,0,,sophistication that you've thought about the subject\Nand realize that the mind alone is unable to solve it.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:59.51,0:30:06.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So the agnostic is integrous in\Nthat he it realizes the limitation of the human intellect
Dialogue: 0,0:30:06.84,0:30:14.23,Default,,0,0,0,,in and of itself cannot handle the question of the\Ninfinite nonlinear domain of consciousness itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:14.32,0:30:16.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?\NIt exists within it.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:16.71,0:30:24.81,Default,,0,0,0,,So how can it answer it when it is within it itself?\NSo the infinite realm of consciousness itself with no
Dialogue: 0,0:30:24.81,0:30:31.26,Default,,0,0,0,,beginning and own end no end is a source of infinite\Npower.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:31.26,0:30:43.21,Default,,0,0,0,,As we have said before one cubic cm of empty space has\Nmore intrinsic power within it than the mass of the
Dialogue: 0,0:30:43.21,0:30:51.16,Default,,0,0,0,,entire universe.\NThose who are interested in the advances of scientific
Dialogue: 0,0:30:51.16,0:30:56.11,Default,,0,0,0,,advances in consciousness,\Nuh there's the new book by the professor of physics at
Dialogue: 0,0:30:56.11,0:31:02.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Berkeley, uh whose name I always forget.\N>> What's his name?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:02.31,0:31:04.39,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Staff.\N>> Henry Stap.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:04.51,0:31:06.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I know.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:06.57,0:31:11.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Henry Staf's new book called Mindful Universe uh\Nintegrates modern science
Dialogue: 0,0:31:11.58,0:31:18.47,Default,,0,0,0,,and consciousness in a very elegant way\Nand is about as sophisticated as you need to get from a
Dialogue: 0,0:31:18.47,0:31:21.31,Default,,0,0,0,,scientific viewpoint.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:21.42,0:31:28.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh the enlightened divine states then the supreme godhead\Nthese all calibrated at a thousand or 5,000
Dialogue: 0,0:31:28.66,0:31:35.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and archangel is 5,000 and up.\Nuh Christ Buddhahood had within this realm uh the great
Dialogue: 0,0:31:35.98,0:31:47.68,Default,,0,0,0,,avatar is calibrated at a thousand um all these are the\Nstates about which man has wondered and written
Dialogue: 0,0:31:47.68,0:32:03.84,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's and they're the most difficult to define\Nbecause that which is uh called uh enlightenment is a
Dialogue: 0,0:32:03.84,0:32:06.63,Default,,0,0,0,,nonlinear condition\Nand there's no one to whom it occurs
Dialogue: 0,0:32:06.63,0:32:15.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and there is no person who becomes enlightened.\NWhat happens is that which is linear disappears
Dialogue: 0,0:32:15.10,0:32:22.95,Default,,0,0,0,,and the linear is replaced by the nonlinear.\NThe nonlinear is a knowingness with neither subject nor
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.95,0:32:30.30,Default,,0,0,0,,predicate nor adjective nor verb.\NIt's a state of being and awareness and it exists in
Dialogue: 0,0:32:30.30,0:32:38.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and of itself and it is not an attribute of any person.\NSo no person becomes enlightened.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:38.18,0:32:45.76,Default,,0,0,0,,What happens is that that\Nwhich was is replaced by an infinite state.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.83,0:33:04.14,Default,,0,0,0,,So the what exists then is this is an infinite state in\Nthe service of which the body speaks and walks around etc.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:06.38,0:33:10.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And this condition comes on unwittingly of its own.\NThere are certain karmic propensities.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:10.23,0:33:15.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course in spiritual work what we try to do is\Nremove the obstacles.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:15.26,0:33:20.73,Default,,0,0,0,,So we don't create an enlightened state.\NWe don't create a enlightened state.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:20.81,0:33:26.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh what happens is we remove the obstacles.\NAnd when you remove the obstacles,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:26.77,0:33:31.77,Default,,0,0,0,,which is the purpose that we're talking today,\Nwhen you remove the obstacles,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:31.77,0:33:36.72,Default,,0,0,0,,then the state it prevails of its own\Nand you really recognize that it's there
Dialogue: 0,0:33:36.72,0:33:41.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and that it's been there all along.\NOrdinarily,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.20,0:33:46.08,Default,,0,0,0,,what you do is you begin to eliminate all conceptual\Nthought.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:46.15,0:33:48.43,Default,,0,0,0,,All conceptual thought.\NWhy?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:48.51,0:33:55.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Because conceptual thought all has to do with appearance\Nand reality has to do with essence.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:55.29,0:33:60.00,Default,,0,0,0,,When we calibrate something,\Nwhat are we we're what we're asking is what is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:00.06,0:34:04.81,Default,,0,0,0,,It's it's its absolute reality.\NWhat is the essence, not the appearance?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:04.88,0:34:11.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we know what appearance looks like.\NIt looks like uh uh the blog blogger world.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:11.13,0:34:16.55,Default,,0,0,0,,What do they call the blogger world?\NInternet bloggerism.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:16.55,0:34:20.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Whatever that is.\NIt charters away about appearance.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:20.23,0:34:26.55,Default,,0,0,0,,You know,\Nit goes from ridiculous to absurd to uh some sometimes at
Dialogue: 0,0:34:26.55,0:34:34.04,Default,,0,0,0,,least factually accurate.\NBut what it's talking about is what a thing appears uh to
Dialogue: 0,0:34:34.04,0:34:37.71,Default,,0,0,0,,be.\NNancy, the former president's wife,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:37.71,0:34:42.55,Default,,0,0,0,,who was in feeble condition, you know,\Nand then the internet came on saying things that were
Dialogue: 0,0:34:42.55,0:34:46.26,Default,,0,0,0,,so spectacularly horrible.\NYou can't believe they were said.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:46.33,0:34:52.33,Default,,0,0,0,,and and then suddenly they disappeared.\NSo at least there's a bit of sanity left someplace to say
Dialogue: 0,0:34:52.33,0:34:55.83,Default,,0,0,0,,such wicked things about people, you know.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:55.93,0:35:03.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So appearance then has nothing to do with reality.\NAnd we what we try to teach you in these co classes is
Dialogue: 0,0:35:03.32,0:35:07.93,Default,,0,0,0,,the difference between appearance and essence.\NWhat a thing looks like
Dialogue: 0,0:35:07.93,0:35:14.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and what it is are two widely divergent things.\NAnd frankly without calibrating the level of
Dialogue: 0,0:35:14.20,0:35:21.13,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness uh very often it's impossible to to tell\Nwhether a thing is true or not true.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:21.21,0:35:27.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And uh everybody can put their hand on a stack of Bibles\Nand then lie.
